    Calculate NWCA 2011 vascular plant metrics based on form V-2

    calcVascPlantMets.Rd

    This function calculates the NWCA 2011 vascular plant metrics. It assumes input data are organized so that each row represents the cover for a single taxon within a single plot at a site. It also assumes a single column is used to identify each unique sample.

    calcVascPlantMets(
  vascIn,
  taxon_name,
  taxaIn = taxaNWCA,
  taxaNat = ccNatNWCA,
  taxaCC = ccNatNWCA,
  taxaWIS = wisNWCA,
  sampID = "UID",
  state = "STATE",
  coeReg = "USAC_REGION",
  cValReg = "NWC_CREG"
)

    Arguments

    vascIn

    A data frame with the following variables (at a minimum):

    • sampID: Variable(s) identified in sampID argument, 'UID' by default

    • PLOT: plot number

    • Variable named in state: Two-letter state postal code of site, used to link native status to taxa in native status taxalist (inNat)

    • Variable named in coeReg: U.S. Army Corps of Engineers region abbreviation for sample, to correspond to GEOG_ID in Wetland Indicator Status taxalist (inWIS)

    • Variable named in cValReg: NWCA C-value regions: values must match GEOG_ID in C-value taxalist (inCVal)

    • Variable named in taxon_name: Taxon name, must match with taxa data frame

    • COVER: value from 0 to 100 indicating relative cover of taxon within plot). Data should already be summed by UID, PLOT, and USDA_NAME.

    taxon_name

    String containing the name of variable for taxon name in

    taxaIn

    A data frame containing taxonomy of all taxa found in vascIn, with the following variables at a minimum:

    • USDA_NAME: USDA accepted name of taxon in sample

    • FAMILY: family name of taxon

    • GENUS: genus name of taxon

    • CATEGORY: USDA PLANTS category

    • GROWTH_HABIT: growth habit as designated in USDA PLANTS

    • DURATION: duration as designated by USDA PLANTS

    If this data frame is not supplied, the data set taxaNWCA included in the package is used.

    taxaNat

    A data frame containing native status as assigned for NWCA for all taxa in vascIn, with the following variables, at a minimum:

    • USDA_NAME: USDA accepted name

    • GEOG_ID: state to which value applies

    • NWCA_NATSTAT: state- and taxon-specific native status

    If this data frame is not supplied, the data set ccNWCA included in the package is used.

    taxaCC

    A data frame containing Coefficient of Conservatism as assigned for NWCA for all taxa in vascIn, with the following variables, at a minimum:

    • USDA_NAME: USDA accepted name

    • GEOG_ID: cValReg to which value applies

    • NWCA_CC: state- and taxon-specific Coefficient of Conservatism

    If this data frame is not supplied, the data set ccNWCA included in the package is used.

    taxaWIS

    A data frame containing Wetland Indicator Status as assigned by USAC and reconciled by USDA PLANTS, with the following variables, at a minimum:

    • USDA_NAME: USDA accepted name

    • GEOG_ID: USAC region to which value applies

    • WIS: Wetland Indicator Status

    If this data frame is not supplied, the data set wisNWCA included in the package is used.

    sampID

    A character vector containing the name(s) of variable(s) necessary to identify unique samples, 'UID' by default

    state

    String containing the name of the state in vascIn, with default value of 'STATE'

    coeReg

    String containing the name of the U.S. Army Corps of Engineers region in vascIn associated with Wetland Indicator Status, with default value of 'USAC_REGION'

    cValReg

    String containing the name of the variable in taxaCC which specifies the C-value region.

    Value

    Either a character string containing an error message when metric calculation is not successful, or a data frame. The first column(s) of the data frame contain the sampID variables, and subsequent columns are named for each metric and contain metric values. A list of vascular plant metrics is installed with the package. Use system.file("Vascular_Plant_Metric_Descriptions.pdf", package="aquametNWCA") to locate the file.

    References

    US Environmental Protection Agency. 2016. National Wetland Condition Assessment: 2011 Technical Report. EPA-843-R-15-006. US Environmental Protection Agency, Washington, DC.

    Author

    Karen Blocksom blocksom.karen@epa.gov

)
